  Putting together the different solutions. When changing the cursor, it is being reset before a command is executed. Also, `ZLE_STATE` is being leveraged to check if we're in replace mode. I'm considering calling `zle reset-prompt` from `zle-line-init` should be avoided. Overriding widgets should also be avoided, as we might have other custom code setting them up. The way widgets preserve previous set ups allows both solutions below to be sourced one after the other.\
  \
  #### Change cursor style\
  \
  ```bash\
  _set_cursor_style_preexec() {\
    builtin print -n '\e[0 q' # default cursor\
  }\
  autoload -Uz add-zsh-hook && add-zsh-hook preexec _set_cursor_style_preexec\
  \
  _set_cursor_style() {\
    case ${KEYMAP} in\
      vicmd|visual) print -n '\e[1 q' ;; # block cursor\
      viins|main)\
        if [[ ${ZLE_STATE} == *overwrite* ]]; then\
          print -n '\e[3 q' # underline cursor\
        else\
          print -n '\e[5 q' # bar cursor\
        fi\
        ;;\
      *) print -n '\e[5 q' ;; # bar cursor\
    esac\
  }\
  for zhook in line-init line-finish keymap-select; do\
    if [[ ! -v functions[_set_cursor_style_${zhook}] ]]; then\
      functions[_set_cursor_style_${zhook}]=${widgets[zle-${zhook}]#user:}'\
  _set_cursor_style'\
      zle -N zle-${zhook} _set_cursor_style_${zhook}\
    fi\
  done\
  unset zhook\
  ```\
  \
  #### Show indicator in prompt\
  \
  ```bash\
  if [[ ! -v functions[_prompt_vimode_keymap-select] ]]; then\
    functions[_prompt_vimode_keymap-select]=${widgets[zle-keymap-select]#user:}'\
  zle reset-prompt\
  zle -R'\
    zle -N zle-keymap-select _prompt_vimode_keymap-select\
  fi\
  \
  _prompt_vimode() {\
    case ${KEYMAP} in\
      vicmd) print -n -- '-- NORMAL --' ;;\
      *)\
        if [[ ${ZLE_STATE} == *overwrite* ]]; then\
          print -n -- '-- REPLACE --'\
        else\
          print -n -- '-- INSERT --'\
        fi\
        ;;\
    esac\
  }\
  RPS1='$(_prompt_vimode)'\
  ```\
  \
  Instead of setting `RPS1`, you might want to prepend the indicator to the left prompt with:\
  \
  ```bash\
  PS1='$(_prompt_vimode) '${PS1}\
  ```\
